You are working inside an Eleventy (11ty) project that must be fully editable inside GrapesJS.

Assume:
- approval_policy: never
- Commit directly to main
- Do NOT create branches or ask questions

===================================
üìÅ PROJECT STRUCTURE & FILE RULES
===================================

All work happens in this structure:

src/
  pages/*.html        ‚Üê all pages (index, about, contact, etc.)
  _layouts/base.njk   ‚Üê single global layout
  _partials/head.html
  _partials/header.html
  _partials/footer.html

css/
js/
images/
lib/        ‚Üê only if needed after cleanup

Output directory: public/

Passthrough: /css, /js, /images, /assets (if present).

FILE LOCATION RULES:
- Pages: always in src/pages/ with .html extension (Nunjucks allowed).
- Partials: only in src/_partials/.
- Layout: only src/_layouts/base.njk.
- You may freely update head.html, header.html, footer.html, base.njk, and any page in src/pages/.

===================================
üìÑ PAGE GENERATION RULES
===================================

For each page (index.html, about.html, contact.html, etc.):

1) Use this front-matter:
---
layout: ../_layouts/base.njk
title: "Page Title"
permalink: "/page.html"
extra_css: []
extra_js: []
---

2) Each page MUST have at least 4‚Äì5 clear content sections, e.g.:
   - Hero / Top banner
   - Features / Services
   - About / Info
   - Testimonials / Logos / Social proof
   - FAQ
   - Call-to-action (CTA)

3) CONTACT PAGE FORM RULE:
If a page has a contact form, it MUST use:

<form id="contactForm"
      class="custom-contact-form"
      data-form-handler
      data-api=""
      data-from="noreply@example.com"
      data-success="Thank you! We will get back to you soon."
      data-error="Oops! Something went wrong."
      data-report-label="template-form">

  <!-- Form fields here -->

</form>

This structure must be preserved so JS can handle submission.

===================================
üß± LAYOUT & PARTIALS
===================================

Create and maintain exactly ONE of each:

- src/_partials/head.html
- src/_partials/header.html
- src/_partials/footer.html

base.njk must:

- Include head, header, and footer partials
- Render page content as:
  <main>
    {{ content | safe }}
  </main>
- Load global CSS/JS:
  - /css/header.css
  - /css/footer.css
  - /js/base.js
  - /js/form-handler.js
- Loop and include any extra_css / extra_js arrays from front-matter without duplicates.

HEADER RULE:
- src/_partials/header.html must be plain, valid HTML for the nav (no Eleventy-specific placeholder logic in the markup).
- Navigation must be styled via /css/header.css (e.g., forced background, high z-index, cleaned toggler styles).

===================================
üîÅ HTML ‚Üí ELEVENTY CONVERSION
===================================

For each imported static HTML theme page:

1) Extract the real main content (central container) and put it in src/pages/*.html.
2) Remove duplicated head/header/footer markup; use base.njk + partials instead.
3) Rewrite asset URLs as root-relative:
   - /css/...
   - /js/...
   - /images/...

Eleventy pages must preserve:
- Original look & layout
- Menus and URLs
- Interactive behavior (as much as possible without jQuery-only plugins)

===================================
üñº GRAPESJS EDITABILITY & IMAGES
===================================

GOAL: All visual content must be easily editable in GrapesJS.

1) All meaningful images must be <img> elements in the HTML.
   - Do NOT hide key images inside CSS background-image.
   - Example:
     ‚ùå style="background-image: url('/images/carousel-1.jpg');"
     ‚úÖ <img src="/images/carousel-1.jpg" alt="...">

2) If CSS previously used background-image for key visuals, move them into <img> tags in the HTML structure instead.

3) For overlay/hover effects that might block clicks in the editor:
   - Overlays can use:
     pointer-events: none;
     z-index: 0;
   - Ensure the <img> itself remains easily clickable in GrapesJS.

4) Restructure/move assets:
   - /assets/images/* ‚Üí /images/*
   - /img/* ‚Üí /images/*
   - Update all paths in HTML/CSS/JS accordingly.
   - No images should remain in nested, theme-specific folders once migrated.

===================================
üß∑ ICONS & FONTS (FLATICON ‚Üí FA6)
===================================

1) Remove Flaticon:
   - Remove all flaticon CSS and font files.
   - Delete /lib/flaticon/* and flaticon.css (or equivalent).
   - Replace all .flaticon-* icon classes with Font Awesome 6 equivalents (use appropriate fa-solid / fa-regular / fa-brands classes).

2) In head.html, include CDN fonts only (no local /fonts folder):

<link rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/icomoon/1.0.0/style.min.css">
<link rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.1/css/all.min.css"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
      referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />

3) Ensure any icon markup in HTML and CSS is updated to use the new Font Awesome classes.

===================================
üì¶ BOOTSTRAP 4 ‚Üí BOOTSTRAP 5 CLEANUP
===================================

Update markup and attributes:

- data-toggle   ‚Üí data-bs-toggle
- data-target   ‚Üí data-bs-target
- mr-*          ‚Üí me-*
- ml-*          ‚Üí ms-*
- form-group    ‚Üí mb-3 (or equivalent modern spacing)

Ensure dropdowns and togglers have correct ARIA attributes for Bootstrap 5 patterns.

===================================
üé† CAROUSEL MODERNIZATION (NO OWL)
===================================

Remove jQuery-only carousel code:

- Delete /lib/owlcarousel/* and /lib/waypoints/*, /lib/counterup/* if only used with jQuery/Owl.
- Remove jQuery-dependent scripts from pages and extra_js.

Convert Owl-style markup:

OLD:
<div class="categories-carousel owl-carousel">
  <!-- items -->
</div>

NEW:
<div class="categories-carousel carousel-scroll">
  <button class="carousel-nav prev" type="button" aria-label="Previous">‚Äπ</button>
  <div class="carousel-track">
    <!-- original item blocks go here -->
  </div>
  <button class="carousel-nav next" type="button" aria-label="Next">‚Ä∫</button>
</div>

Add to main CSS:
- scroll-snap based horizontal scrolling
- flex layout for .carousel-track
- responsive item sizing
- simple styles for .carousel-nav buttons

Add to /js/main.js (no jQuery):
- On DOMContentLoaded, attach click handlers to each carousel‚Äôs nav buttons.
- Scroll the track left/right by ~80% of its width.

In GrapesJS, even without JS, carousel items must appear visible and editable in the editor.

